  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      At the intensive care unit (ICU) fluoroquinolone antibiotics, like levofloxacin, are
      frequently used for the treatment of infections.

      Adequate blood levels are required for a good efficacy of the antibiotic. Due to the fact
      that levofloxacin is almost completely eliminated renally, the blood levels for this
      antibiotic are strongly influenced by the renal function. Therefore, this study aims to
      evaluate the pharmacokinetics of levofloxacin in patients with hyperfiltration, in comparison
      with critically ill patients with normal renal function.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
